The paper discusses the use of Belousov-Zhabotinsky (BZ) reaction, an excitable chemical medium, for unconventional computing devices. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the use of BZ reaction for characterizing the geometry of street networks, which could fall under the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of BZ reaction for image processing, logical circuits, and robot controllers, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of BZ reaction for cluster analysis, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between the network geometry and traffic flow of Tehran, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
